SIMPLE: hypostatical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypostatical
<hw>Hy`po*stat"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>hypostatique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to hypostasis,
or substance; hence, constitutive, or elementary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The grand doctrine of the chymists, touching their three
<qex>hypostatical</qex> principles.</q> <rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Personal, or distinctly personal; relating to the
divine hypostases, or substances.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Pearson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Depending upon, or due to,
deposition or setting; <as>as, <ex>hypostatic</ex> cognestion,
cognestion due to setting of blood by gravitation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hypostatic union</b></col> <fld>(Theol.)</fld>, <cd>the
union of the divine with the human nature of Christ.</cd>
<rj><au>Tillotson.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypostatically</ent>⟦br⟧
